Popular singer Iyanya has said that it will be a dream come through for him to be in the studio cooking up a record with American singer Usher Raymond. The Senior Special Assistant on Tourism and Entertainment to Cross River Governor made this known in a recent Instagram live interview. While listing his favorite all-time collaborators in and outside Africa, he said: “I definitely want to do a song with 2baba, Diamond Platnumz. We had a discussion the other day and I am looking forward to collaborating with him and anybody willing to collaborate, it is a good time.”   I don’t regret featuring Zinoleesky in Good Time- Mulla Rae     Work the only ritual for money- Vector     Ebuka: BBNaija not instant success gate pass   Continuing he said: “In the United State of America, Usher, ‘8701 is still a classic album and it changed my life. I’ll be blessed, it will be a dream come through being in the studio with Usher just making music. Inspiration beside usher coming up Marques Houston, Ginuwine and in the United Kingdom, Skepta.” Sharing his goal for 2022, Iyanya said he is working with his team on an EP as many of his fans have been yearning for a new song from him. The ‘Kukere’ star also averred that COVID-19 made him a better person saying the period opened his eyes to so many things as he’s thankful for life and the opportunity to reach out to people.